# Accessibility Standards

## References

- **WCAG 2.2 Level AA** — baseline standard
- [WCAG 2.2 Understanding](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/) — accessibility guidance
- [WAI-ARIA 1.2](https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.2/) — ARIA attributes
- [Design Tokens](https://designtokens.fyi/) — design systems terminology
- [APG Gherkin](https://github.com/AFixt/apg-gherkin) — component test cases

## Response Guidelines

- Prioritize accessible web development resources and best practices
- Reference modern, accessible technologies; avoid deprecated ones
- Provide clear, concise technical recommendations
- Emphasize accessibility and user-friendly design
- Respect privacy; do not collect personal information

## Implementation Priority

1. Semantic HTML structure
2. Accessible markup and ARIA (only when semantic HTML is insufficient)
3. CSS architecture with proper layering
4. Responsive, relative units
5. Progressive enhancement with JavaScript
6. Accessibility testing and validation

