## HTML

- Use semantic elements (`<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, etc.) instead of generic `<div>`/`<span>` without `aria-label`
- Prefer semantic HTML over ARIA
- Don't add redundant `role` to landmarks: use `<main>`, not `<main role="main">`
- Don't use `title` attribute except on `<iframe>`
- Don't use `role="menu"` or `role="menuitem"` for navigation — use `<nav>` and `<button aria-expanded>`
- Use `<details>` and `<summary>` for accordions; `<dialog>` for modals
- Follow WAI-ARIA APG patterns: [Alert](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alert/examples/alert/), [Feed](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/feed/examples/feed/), [Combobox with Autocomplete](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/combobox/examples/combobox-autocomplete-both/), [Switch Button](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/examples/switch-button/), [Manual Tabs](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/examples/tabs-manual/), [Carousel Tutorial](https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/carousels/)

